f(x,y,z) = x^2 + y^2 + z^2
f
\nabla f=(2x, 2y, 2z)
P_0=(0,0,0)
f
\nabla^2 f= \begin{bmatrix}         2 & 0 & 0 \\         0 & 2 & 0 \\         0 & 0 & 2 \\ \end{bmatrix} 
P_0
\alpha_1 = det \begin{bmatrix} 2\\ \end{bmatrix} = 2 \gt 0 
\alpha_2 = \det \begin{bmatrix} 2 & 0\\ 0 & 2\\ \end{bmatrix} = 4 \gt 0 
\alpha_3 = \det \begin{bmatrix} 2 & 0 & 0\\ 0 & 2 & 0\\ 0 & 0 & 2 \end{bmatrix} = 8 \gt 0 
P_0
f
0
f(0,0,0) = 0
